## File Structure

```
solidity-data-types-dictionary.html    # Complete standalone application
README.md                               # This file
Solidity_Data_Types_Dictionary.docx     # Printable Word document version
```

## Customization

The HTML file is self-contained with inline CSS and JavaScript. To customize:

- **Colors**: Modify the CSS variables in the `:root` selector
- **Content**: Edit the `typesData` object in the `<script>` section
- **Styling**: All styles are in the `<style>` block

## Adding New Types

To add a new type, locate the `typesData` object and add an entry:

```javascript
{
  name: "yourType",
  badge: "value",  // or "reference" or "special"
  description: "Brief description",
  example: `// Code example here`,
  useCase: "When to use this type",
  tip: "Optional helpful tip",
  gasNote: "Optional gas optimization note"
}
```

